<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Lick" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Lick,</orth> to pass over with the tongue: <bibl n="shak. ven 915" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 915</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 2, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 2, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.156" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 156</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.2.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 2, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.2.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 2, 4</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 4.2.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 2, 4</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.2.42" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 2, 42</bibl>. <emph>to l. up</emph> == to consume: <cit><quote>may diseases l. up their false bloods,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.539" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 539</bibl></cit>.
